title: Great budget mouse! Been using for two years, and still running!
body: I'm writing this review after TWO YEARS of usage, and I got this in an discounted sale, for around 180 bucks that time :) A medium sized mouse that's good for large hands like mine! if u really want a mouse and you're under a TIGHT BUDGET, just go for this one, its an amazing and really LONG LASTING. Clean look, LIGHTWEIGHT, but yet plasticky, and click sounds are quite loud, scroll bar isnt so smooth, but under this budget, couldn't expect more and it really does the job, and I almost got used to all of the above mentioned cons eventually, and extremely surprised by its LONGEVITY, cuz generally mouses of this price didn't last long for me, not even a year, they stop working. But this isn't one of them. Pro tip, UNLESS AND UNTIL YOU HANDLE IT REALLY GOOD, AND HAVE THE PRACTICE OF KEEPIN IT PACKED OR BOXED IN A SAFE PLACE WHEN NOT IN USE, ANY MOUSE WOULD MALFUNCTION SOONER, just treat this mouse like any other mouse you'll get for thousands of bucks, it will last longer :) Great for PROFESSIONAL USE, video and photo editing, etc. Not so great for gaming, for playing games like Rainbow Six Seige, Valorant etc., due to less precision and response time(tested it, still you can manage to do well upto an extent, depends on how good of a gamer you are to understand and get used to the latency and response time of your mouse over time), but still you can obviously play some good old offline story mode games like GTA V. I'm a designer and I use it mostly for rendering, and modeling stuff, surprisingly this mouse seemed to do a great job for the price. Back then when I bought this, there were barely 100 reviews, and now I'm actually surprised to see these many reviews on this product. Overall, this is a really good budget mouse, and really really long lasting, as far as my experience at least.
product: Dell MS116 1000DPI USB Wired Optical Mouse

title: Been using it for a few days now ... handles well; no problems so far
body: I bought this in a store close to my home. I didn't purchase it on Amazon. The original MRP listed on the box is Rs 400. But the retailer was selling it for Rs 280. So I believe that is the fair price of the product. My advice is - buy it only from a trusted retailer because there are some people selling fake version of branded mouse products. I had been using a HP mouse for a few years before this and for me the HP mouse gave problems - after a few months of usage the left click started behaving like the right click button. My trust in HP products diminished after that experience. I have used Microsoft mouse too - and it worked for a while until it also broke down. My experience with these branded products drove me to try Dell or Logitech. I told myself it will be one or the other. I went to the retailer and he showed me both and said Dell is the better choice. I don't know what made him say so, and you don't have to go by his word, but I can tell you that if you are looking for a basic mouse under 300 then this is a good choice among the lot. I have been using this only for a few days now so I can't say if it is durable in the long run, but so far I have zero complaints. It does what it is supposed to do and it is easy to handle. It is worth buying if you are just looking for a basic mouse that functions smoothly. Additionally, you can check out the Toshiba or Targus mouse in case you are looking for other options. Logitech is another safe one. Avoid HP - it gives issues after a few months of usage. I speak from experience.
product: Dell MS116 1000DPI USB Wired Optical Mouse

title: A great product
body: Pros - Larger size leads to a better overall grip of the mouse thus leading to a comfortable usage over long periods. Compared to others, it is less bulky, the design is great and it is curved just right to fit well.Con -  the only con I could find is the weight of the product. It is slightly heavier than the other similar products out there, probably because of its size. But that doesn't affect much and you get habituated to it in the long run.Definitely recommendable!
product: Dell MS116 1000DPI USB Wired Optical Mouse

title: Best basic mouse I've used
body: This is the mouse they give us at work. Needless to say, I have spent many hours using it continuously. I can completely vouch for it. It's a very simple device but I think Dell has done a great job with the ergonomics. The mouse has sloping sides which does not go into an "hourglass" shape like some other mice. This makes holding it so much nicer. It fits into the palm well with a lot of support. For <300 rupees you can't go wrong with this mouse.
product: Dell MS116 1000DPI USB Wired Optical Mouse
